<!-- Stacks v2221 --><div id='stacks_out_0_page11' class='stacks_top'><div id='stacks_in_0_page11' class=''><div id='stacks_out_227_page11' class='stacks_out'><div id='stacks_in_227_page11' class='stacks_in '><div id="myExtraContent8"><div id='stacks_out_47_page11' class='stacks_out'><div id='stacks_in_47_page11' class='stacks_in float_left_stack'><div class='stacks_div stacks_float_left'>
<div class='centered_image' ><img class='imageStyle' src='files/stacks_image_48.jpg' width='576' height='614' alt='Stacks Image 48' /></div>
</div>
<span id='stacks_in_49_page11'><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; ">Poet, writer and broadcaster Pat Boran is one of the best-known of his generation of Irish poets. <br /><br />He has published more than a dozen books of poetry and prose &mdash; among them Waveforms: Bull Island Haiku (2015), </span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "><em>The Next Life</em></span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "> (2012) and </span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "><em>A Man is Only As Good: A Pocket Selected Poems </em></span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; ">(2017), as well as the humorous memoir </span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "><em>The Invisible Prison (2009), </em></span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; ">and the popular writers' handbook </span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "><em>The Portable Creative Writing Workshop, </em></span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; ">now in its fourth edition. <br /><br />He is a former presenter of</span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "><em> The Poetry Programme</em></span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "> and </span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "><em>The Enchanted Way </em></span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; ">on RT&Eacute; Radio 1, and works part-time as a literary editor in which capacity he has edited numerous anthologies of poetry and prose, including, with Gerard Smyth, the bestselling anthology </span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "><em>If Ever You Go: A Map of Dublin in Poetry and Song, </em></span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; ">the Dublin: One City, One Book designated title for 2014, and, with Eugene O&rsquo;Connell, </span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "><em>The Deep Heart&rsquo;s Core</em></span><span style="font:14px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; "> (2017).<br /><br />He is a member of Aosd&aacute;na, the Irish affiliation of artists, writers and musicians.<br /><br />Thanks for visiting.</span></span></div></div><div id='stacks_out_809_page11' class='stacks_out'><div id='stacks_in_809_page11' class='stacks_in '><div id='stacks_out_810_page11' class='stacks_out'><div id='stacks_in_810_page11' class='stacks_in com_rapidweavercentral_stacks_bigfootresponsive_1_stack'><!-- Responsive Bigfoot 1 Column Stack by RapidWeaver Central. Visit http://www.weaverthings.com for more information. -->

